WorldStage NewsOnline—- The kidnapped Provost of College of Education, Katsina Ala, Mr Tsavwua Gborigyo, has regained freedom in Benue. The command’s Police Public Relations Office (PPRO) DSP. Ms Catherine Anene, said the provost reunited with his family late Thursday evening. The provost was kidnapped at Ihugh in Vandiekya Local Government Area on his way from a burial ceremony on Aug. 9 Anene disclosed that the provost was released without payment of any ransom. She said investigations were ongoing to apprehend the kidnappers and other criminal elements terrorising the state, and promised to shield the informant with relevant information.